name: Bay Window Room
neighborhood_overview: Small shopping center five minute walk away with a Burger King, Dunkin’ Donuts, CVS pharmacy, Nick’s Restaurant.
description:
Nicely furnished, sunny and comfortable bedroom in a house, in a safe Boston neighborhood 35 minutes from downtown Boston via public transportation - 2 minute walk to MBTA bus which goes to the subway station at Forest Hills. There is a laundromat with an excellent wash, dry, & fold service (not too expensive) close by. Most of the local colleges & universities are within 45 minutes. Parking is available in front of the house on the street. Continental breakfast (cereal, toast, coffee, tea).

The space
Shared bathroom on second floor.
